CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1779891067
OL,3,CSocial media as dangerous for young
OL,4,Cpeople as smoking, top doctors warn
OL,6,FThere have been widespread calls for
OL,7,Fthe UK government to follow
OL,8,FAustralia's lead on a full social
OL,9,Fmedia ban for under-16s, though
OL,10,Fquestions have been raised about its
OL,11,Feffectiveness.
OL,13,FFormer health secretary Wes Streeting,
OL,14,Fwho quit government earlier this month
OL,15,Fand is seen as one of those to replace
OL,16,FSir Keir Starmer, should there be a
OL,17,FLabour leadership challenge, has
OL,18,Fcalled for a partial social media ban,
OL,19,Flikening tech companies to the tobacco
OL,20,Findustry.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/16
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1779891067
OL,3,CSocial media as dangerous for young
OL,4,Cpeople as smoking, top doctors warn
OL,6,F"Social media should be treated like
OL,7,Ftobacco ` it's extremely addictive,
OL,8,Fbad for our health, and Big Tech is
OL,9,Fborrowing the Big Tobacco playbook to
OL,10,Favoid regulation," he said.
OL,12,F"We've got to give our children their
OL,13,Fchildhood back."
OL,15,FHe added that a ban for under-16s
OL,16,F"must be the start, not the end".
OL,18,F"We have given the pen to tech moguls
OL,19,Fto write our future for us. It's time
OL,20,Fto take the pen back."
OL,26,@tD@AOUzD@AOU|D@VO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/16
